      "content": "Even if you feel fine, self-prescribing a \"loading dose\" of 50,000 IU without confirmed blood work is risky because Vitamin D toxicity can silently accumulate and damage your bones and kidneys over weeks. Standard medical protocols specifically require monitoring your serum levels to determine the correct dosage, as what is considered a safe high dose for one person could be dangerous for another. Without professional guidance, you risk overdosing on a nutrient you may not actually need in such quantities, which could have severe long-term health consequences. Please consider visiting a clinic or using a mobile health service for a quick, affordable checkup before taking any high-dose supplements.",
      "source": "target",
